  🇺🇸 ENG


  NixOS-Meowrch V3.4.0: The Stability Update is Live! 🐱🚀


  It’s finally done. I’ve personally finished testing the V3.4.0 release. The last 2–3 days were a total "debugging
  marathon." Porting custom Arch packages to NixOS is a constant battle with hashes, paths, and dependencies, but I’ve
  managed to polish everything to a mirror shine.

  What’s new in this release:


  🔹 Mewline (Dynamic Island): Updated to stable v1.4.1 and fully migrated to a systemd user service. It now features
  automatic restart on failure—if the bar crashes, the system brings it back in 3 seconds.
  🔹 UWSM Integration: We are now using the Universal Wayland Session Manager. The Hyprland session is faster, cleaner,
  and much more reliable.
  🔹 Theming & UI:
      - Restored the original Rofi layout and colors from the Arch version for that authentic Meowrch feel.
      - Fixed SDDM theming: your custom dotfile configs are no longer overwritten during rebuilds.
      - Enforced Dark Mode for stubborn GTK4/Libadwaita apps (like HotkeyHub and GNOME Settings).
  🔹 Maintenance: Added the update-pkgs command. Now you can sync all custom Meowrch components and rebuild the system
  with a single command.
  🔹 Cleanup & Docs: Removed experimental components to slim down the build and completely overhauled the README with
  accurate keybindings and a beginner's guide.

  Testing is complete, and the system is rock solid. Everything is pushed to GitHub.

  Update now: run update-pkgs or use the installer.
  GitHub: https://github.com/Redm00use/NixOS-Meowrch


